{ With the pawns in the centre wedged against
each other, it is on the flanks that break-
throughs are usually made. Often the players
take one flank each and then try to be first to
break through. However, the rule "An attack
on the flank is best answered by a counterat-
tack in the centre" can be relevant even with
a closed centre, as it may be possible to dis-
integrate the centre by sacrificing a piece. }
 *


